{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1d3068f6-8f6a-4793-b61a-59a8b1319c7e","content":"`dotnet-dump` isn't installed, but `dotnet` is available. I don't see a `.dmp` file in the current directory though.\n\nHere's how to proceed:\n\n### 1. Install `dotnet-dump`\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n```\n\n### 2. Analyze the dump\n```bash\ndotnet-dump analyze /path/to/your/file.dmp\n```\n\n### 3. Useful commands inside the analyzer\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `pe` | Print last exception (start here!) |\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `clrthreads` | List all managed threads |\n| `dso` | Dump stack objects |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary |\n| `exit` | Quit |\n\n**Typical workflow:** Run `pe` first to see the exception that caused the crash, then `clrstack` to see where it happened.\n\nWould you like me to install `dotnet-dump` and walk through the analysis interactively? If so, please share the path to your `.dmp` file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"24bd8b73-244d-4ff2-837f-b42189c411ef","outputTokens":274,"requestId":"AC04:18E49A:142FDB0:16AAD2E:6A067281"},"id":"cee41dad-611e-421c-9a8a-58dc9314b372","timestamp":"2026-05-15T01:10:37.410Z","parentId":"04625c36-490b-4e73-bb98-0afc6b1e1a4a"}
